# SYS-LIC-Z3
## License Mutation Controller

Version: 2.0

---

# Overview

SYS-LIC-Z3 serves as the authoritative mutation controller for the HyperSync License Operating System.

Its responsibility is to execute approved license lifecycle mutations after orchestration has been completed by SYS-LIC-Z2. The controller applies validated state changes to the License Registry, manages processing ownership, and produces immutable governance evidence for every completed mutation.

By separating mutation authority from lifecycle orchestration, SYS-LIC-Z3 provides deterministic state transitions, operational consistency, and complete audit traceability.

---

# Architectural Purpose

SYS-LIC-Z3 is responsible for:

• Authoritative Registry Mutation

• Processing Lock Management

• Mutation Contract Validation

• Lifecycle State Application

• Governance Evidence Generation

• Operational Completion

---

# Core Responsibilities

The controller performs the following operational sequence:

- Monitor mutation requests
- Validate operational eligibility
- Acquire processing lock
- Prepare mutation contract
- Apply authoritative registry mutation
- Release processing lock
- Append immutable governance evidence
- Complete lifecycle processing

Every mutation follows a deterministic execution contract before being committed to the authoritative License Registry.

